In [137]:
def parse_log(filename: str, verbose: bool=False) -> pd.DataFrame:
    with open(filename) as f:
        logs = f.readlines()

    report = list()
    elem = dict()
    prev_dt = None
    for log in logs:
        if len(log) < 100:
            continue
        l = log[100:]
        
        timestamp = log[:23]
        dt = datetime.strptime(timestamp, '%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S.%f')
        # if prev_dt is not None:
        #     print(timestamp, dt- prev_dt)
                
        delta = (dt- prev_dt) if prev_dt is not None else None
        # duration = (delta.hours*60 + delta.minutes + delta.seconds/60) if delta is not None else None
        duration = delta.seconds if delta is not None else None
        if "Training" in l:
            # print(l)
            elem = dict(training_loss=float(l.rsplit(" ",2)[-1]), training_time=duration)
            continue
        elif "Accuracy" in l:
            # print(l)
            elem.update(dict(
                validation_loss=float(l.rsplit(" ",2)[-1])), 
                accuracy=float(l.split(" ", 3)[-2]),
                validation_time=duration        
            )
            report.append(elem)

        prev_dt = dt
        
    df = pd.DataFrame(report)
    df = df.reset_index()
    df = df.rename(columns={"index":"epoch"})
    df.epoch = df.epoch+1
    if verbose:
        print(
            f"Summary:\n"
            f" - epochs: {len(df)}\n"
            f" - best acc: {df.accuracy.max()} %\n"
            f" - time elapsed: ", end=""
        )
        if int(df.training_time.sum()+df.validation_time.sum())//3600 > 0 :
            print(
                f"{(int(df.training_time.sum()+df.validation_time.sum()))//3600:d} hr ", end="" 
            )
        print(
            f"{int((df.training_time.sum()+df.validation_time.sum())%3600)//60} min " 
            f"(avg: {(df.training_time.mean()+df.validation_time.mean())/60:.1f} min)\n"
        )
    
    return df
In [138]:
def draw_lineplot(df:pd.DataFrame):
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(1,2, sharex=True, figsize=(16,4))
    sns.lineplot(df, x=df.epoch, y=df.training_loss, label="training loss", ax=axes[0])
    sns.lineplot(df, x=df.epoch, y=df.validation_loss, label="vailidation loss", ax=axes[0])
    sns.lineplot(df, x=df.epoch, y=df.accuracy, label="accuracy(%)", c="r", ax=axes[1])
